records.addlTxt:
Defendant Michael A Pufahl in court, in custody, with attorney J Anthony Rosario.   Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

7 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 53 days)
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  5 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:  Jetz Convenience Store and Samantha A.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Letter of Apology to Samantha A. to be completed immediately through his attorney.

RESTITUTION:  To be determined;

COURT COSTS:  $278.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

The Court sets the matter for a restitution hearing and the Defendant to appear by video.  The victim in the case may file an affidavit regarding restitution within the next 2 weeks.  Attorney Rosario to contact the Court in writing if the restitution is not requested in good faith.
